content: The patient is a right‑hand dominant horticulturalist who sustained a trip and fall on 6/21/25 while leaving Groundlings, resulting in left wrist pain. The pain was present immediately after the fall, was painful then, and began to improve slightly. She obtained urgent‑care X‑rays that showed no fractures and was diagnosed with a sprain. Subsequent exposure to humidity in Massachusetts increased her pain, prompting evaluation today.
title: HPI Spencer

content: On exam, left upper extremity skin is clean and intact without erythema or hematemosis. No specific tendon inflammation. Mild tendon inflammation over the ECU tendon. Um, there is pain with pro-supination. No evidence of subluxation of the ECU tendon. Excellent range of motion overall.
title: Musculoskeletal

content: X-rays are normal through these, the wrist, left wrist.
title: Imaging Results

content: We'll call it left ECU tendonitis, left ulnar-sided wrist pain. Recommend trial of hand therapy. Recommend MRI for further evaluation. Return to clinic after MRI.
